Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover with the lid
and bring to the boil on medium-high heat. Once boiling, turn the heat down to
its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from
the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until
ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{2}. Heat a #large frying pan{}
over medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @Sesame Seeds{10%g} and dry-fry,
stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> Watch the sesame seeds like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Transfer the seeds to a #small bowl{} and set the pan aside.

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(stalks and all). Pop into a #medium bowl{} along with
the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g}. Add the @Olive Oil{1/2%tbsp}, @Sugar for the Dressing{1/2%tsp},
@Rice Vinegar{1%tbsp} and half the sesame seeds. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then mix well to dress.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the (now empty) #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
Season the @Pork Steak{2} with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Once hot, add the pork steaks and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on each
side. Reduce the heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{4-5%minutes}, turning
every couple of mins.

> The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the pork is cooked, drain off any excess fat. Add the @Teriyaki Sauce{75%ml} to
the pan, bring to a boil and bubble until the pork is coated in the glaze,
~{1-2%minutes}. Once cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with another plate
or foil to rest.

When rested, slice each steak widthways. Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share
between your #bowls{}, then top with the slaw and sliced pork. Spoon over any
glaze left in the pan and sprinkle over the spring onion and remaining
@Sesame Seeds{5%g}. Enjoy!